## Core Principles

### 1. Backward Compatibility
- NEVER break existing functionality
- Test changes against existing user workflows
- Preserve database schema unless absolutely necessary
- Keep existing API contracts intact
- Maintain existing component props/interfaces

### 2. Incremental Improvements
- Make small, focused changes
- Fix one bug at a time
- Improve one component/page at a time
- Test thoroughly before moving to the next
- Document changes for team awareness

### 3. TypeScript Strictness
- Fix `any` types → use proper types
- Add missing type definitions
- Use type guards for runtime safety
- Export types for reusability
- Fix type errors, don't suppress them with `@ts-ignore`

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const user: any = await getUser()

// ✅ GOOD
interface User {
  id: string
  email: string
  role: 'admin' | 'agency' | 'volunteer'
}
const user: User | null = await getUser()
```

### 4. Code Quality Over Speed
- Write clean, maintainable code
- Add comments for complex logic
- Extract repeated code into utilities
- Use meaningful variable names
- Keep functions small and focused

