## Performance Optimization

### 1. Identify Performance Issues
Common performance problems to fix:
- **Large bundle sizes:** Dynamic imports for heavy components
- **Unnecessary re-renders:** Use React.memo, useMemo, useCallback
- **Slow queries:** Add database indexes, optimize queries
- **Unoptimized images:** Use Next.js Image component
- **Too many requests:** Batch requests, implement caching
- **Memory leaks:** Clean up subscriptions, intervals, listeners

### 2. Image Optimization
```typescript
// ❌ BAD
<img src="/logo.png" alt="Logo" />

// ✅ GOOD
import Image from 'next/image'
<Image 
  src="/logo.png" 
  alt="DiasporaBase Logo" 
  width={200} 
  height={50}
  priority={isAboveFold}
  placeholder="blur"
/>
```

### 3. Code Splitting
```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Heavy modal loaded upfront
import ProjectModal from './ProjectModal'

// ✅ GOOD - Lazy load modal
const ProjectModal = dynamic(() => import('./ProjectModal'), {
  loading: () => <div>Loading...</div>
})
```

### 4. Database Query Optimization
```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Fetching everything
const { data } = await supabase.from('projects').select('*')

// ✅ GOOD - Fetch only needed columns
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('projects')
  .select('id, title, description, agency_id, created_at')
  .order('created_at', { ascending: false })
  .limit(20)
```

### 5. Caching Strategy
```typescript
// For data that doesn't change often
export const revalidate = 3600 // Revalidate every hour

// For real-time data
export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'

// Use React Cache for duplicate requests
import { cache } from 'react'
